<quantity id="236CB5EF5167180AFE27FE9AED3A1D58" box="[446,514,261,287]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long. Colour (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F5167180AFD29FE9AECF61D67" box="[688,974,260,288]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 258, 259, 266, 267</figureCitation>
): pronotum orange to yellow with wide median dark marking extending to both anterior and posterior margins; MN and MS paler yellow; elytra very dark brown; head between eyes black (antennae and mouthparts incomplete); venter of thorax brown, legs pale yellowish-brown with slightly darker brown tarsi; ventrites anterior to LO with median darker markings, extending to sides with narrow anterolateral patch pale in 
<date id="902A3ECA5167180AFD29FE0BEDED1DE8" box="[688,725,404,431]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V5</date>
, with pale lateral margin (approx.1/4 ventrite width) in 
<date id="902A3ECA5167180AFAD3FE0AEA541DE8" box="[1354,1388,405,431]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V4</date>
and median dark marking occupying less than 1/3 ventrite width in 
<date id="902A3ECA5167180AFCCFFE26EC441D94" box="[854,892,441,467]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V3</date>
; terminal tergites pale. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F5167180AFB65FE26EFFE1DBF" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 258, 266, 267</figureCitation>
): subparallel sided, width less than humeral width. Elytron: parallel sided; interstitial lines 1, 2 visible but not as well elevated as suture. Head: GHW 
<date id="902A3ECA5167180AFDC5FD9EED471E5C" box="[604,639,513,539]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">6 x</date>
SIW; ASD &lt;ASW. Antennae incomplete. Legs incomplete. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F5167180AFF39FDBAEE3D1E78" box="[160,261,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Fig. 259</figureCitation>
): short rounded MPP present on 
<date id="902A3ECA5167180AFDE6FDBAED901E78" box="[639,680,549,575]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V7.</date>
T8 (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F5167180AFD78FDBAEC7E1E07" box="[737,838,549,576]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Fig. 268</figureCitation>
): with elongate slender anterolateral arms which are longer than the posterior entire part of T8; posterior margin entire, median area rounded and produced a little beyond rounded corners.Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F5167180AFD82FDF2EDD71EC0" box="[539,751,620,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 260, 261, 265</figureCitation>
): sternite terminated by elongated medially emarginated hairy lobe; median anterior margin of tergite prolonged and apically truncate. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F5167180AFBC0FD0EEBC71EEB" box="[1113,1279,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 262−264</figureCitation>
): ML wide in basal ¾, narrowing in apical ¼ where it is ¼ as wide as basal portion; apices of LL narrowed and strongly divergent; ML considerably shorter than LL.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AC8E4B815167180AFF5EFD62EFED1FC4" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E42B180A5167180AFF5EFD62EFED1FC4" blockId="92.[151,1437,152,899]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185167180AFF5EFD62EE0C1F50" bold="true" box="[199,308,765,791]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Remarks</emphasis>
. The Indian specimen is included here because of similarities in colour pattern to the 
<typeStatus id="3B2FA6A85167180AFB6CFD62EA101F50" box="[1269,1320,765,791]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">type</typeStatus>
, and similarities in genitalic patterns to the 
<collectingRegion id="2650D6E85167180AFD8AFCBEED0C1F7C" box="[531,564,801,827]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lankan specimen. The 
<typeStatus id="3B2FA6A85167180AFCA6FCBEEC571F7C" box="[831,879,801,827]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">type</typeStatus>
was not dissected and assignments made here are based on similarity of general habitus only. The 
<collectingRegion id="2650D6E85167180AFD2DFCDAEDED1F18" box="[692,725,837,863]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lankan male in NHML was standing under a 
<taxonomicName id="239463895167180AFB47FCDAEAA41F18" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1888" box="[1246,1436,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirticeps">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185167180AFB47FCDAEAA41F18" box="[1246,1436,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Luciola hirticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
label.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
